North Korea is a different situation. You can tell it's posturing because they make grandiose announcements. If they intended to start shit, they wouldn't say they were withdrawing from the nuclear nonproliferation treat, they wouldn't see they are doing missle testing. They'd just do it on the sly and catch us off guard.<br>
<br>
I've been told that this is noise simply to get the fuel and food that we have deprived the north from having. The US is not being very nice, cutting them off so harshly, and they only have one card to play, nukes. <br>
<br>
The North knows if they start shooting off nukes, the US will obliterate them. So they won't be stupid. <br>
<br>
Saddam, OTOH, doesn't really care. This is a guy who invaded two neighbors (Iran and Kuwait), gassed his own people and quite possibly IS in league with Al Qaeda.<br>
<br>
At this point, I'll give Bush the benefit of the doubt. He's not doing this to distract us from his scandals, unlike his predecessor. He can't reveal the intelligence he has because it's come, in all likelihood, from agents within Iraq who could be exposed if Bush shows his hand. <br>
<br>
But after the war (war? please. It will be a one-sided ass kicking even worse than in 91), I want some answers. I want the intelligence that justifies all of the lost lives. I want to see what evidence he had to go through with this. And then he better end the blockade of Iraq and let the Red Cross in full tilt, so they can help the people of that country, who are innocent in all this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eadrictheranger>Eadric the Ranger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tolapumj wanna-be</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(1/14/03 2:56:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=795.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT - Opposed to the war with Iraq? Heres what you can do</span><hr size=1> [quote]But after the war (war? please. It will be a one-sided ass kicking even worse than in 91)[/quote]<br>
